I am a fan of Arena, but I'm of the mindset that profit considerations drive a lot of the decision-making surrounding the game.  In a dev FAQ that was recently posted to Reddit, there was a question as to why booster packs bought in-game are only eight cards. The PR person answered that this was to avoid "overwhelming" new players with the sheer number of cards that a full booster pack would provide.
Granted, an Arena booster still contains 1x rare and 2x uncommon, but the answer kind of stinks of money-grubbing.

They've said Brawl is on their agenda though, so I'm hopeful. It's whatever. I log onto Arena an hour or less nightly after work to just blow off some steam and apparently wreck face with the new cheap Mono U deck that's making the rounds.
